It turned out that with the USB-C-Breakout, which I used to connect the charger, 5V and GND were swapped on the Silkscreen.
I swapped the cables and now the charging indicator is lit.
The ESP did not go online immediately. Let's wait for a few minutes.
It's been an hour and it's still offline.
It looks like it's rebooting and triggering a Tasmota reset function.
I think the panel just doesn't work. I've now ordered a larger one and hope that one will work then.
Take a look at what I found in my workshop.
A 24-V panel. Unfortunately, the sun is already so low (and partially obscured by a tree) that the value practically drops to zero as soon as I put the device into operation.
I'll probably have to wait until tomorrow to see if it's sufficient for this setup or if I need the better panel that I ordered.
According to Amazon, I bought the panel in 2021 and it should deliver 12 V at a maximum of 1.2 A.
