Oh look! The thing went online about an hour ago for about half a minute.
Maybe the panel just charged the battery long enough for 38 seconds of runtime. It took it more than two hours to do that.
Ratet mal: Today it is cloudy. I am therefore not sure if the (probably broken) solar panel will manage to generate enough electricity at all.
Let's see.
Update: I have installed the new panel and now it seems to be working.
It could still fail as soon as the sun goes down, but let's give it a chance.
